  -n kuma-system \
  --create-namespace \
  -f values.yaml
Verificar:

kubectl get pods -n kuma-system
Esperado:

kuma-control-plane
kuma-dp-injector
kuma-metrics

3️⃣ Expor Control Plane (VMs vão ligar aqui)
Precisas expor KDS.
Service:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: kuma-cp
  namespace: kuma-system
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  ports:
  - port: 5685
    name: kds
  selector:
    app: kuma-control-plane
VMs depois ligam a:

kuma-cp:5685

4️⃣ Instalar Spoke Cluster (Zone)
Cada cluster Talos será uma zone.
values-zone.yaml

controlPlane:
  mode: zone

zone:
  name: cluster-eu1

kdsGlobalAddress: kuma-cp.kuma-system.svc:5685

ingress:
  enabled: true

global:
  image:
    tag: "2.7.0"
Instalar:

helm install kuma kuma/kuma \
  -n kuma-system \
  --create-namespace \
  -f values-zone.yaml

5️⃣ Zone ingress como hostNetwork
Como queres evitar LB e usar nodes via BGP, faz isto:
zone ingress DaemonSet

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: DaemonSet
metadata:
  name: kuma-zone-ingress
  namespace: kuma-system
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: kuma-zone-ingress
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: kuma-zone-ingress
    spec:
      hostNetwork: true
      containers:
      - name: envoy
        image: envoyproxy/envoy:v1.30
        ports:
        - containerPort: 10001
Assim cada node terá:

Envoy zone ingress
hostNetwork
Routers podem mandar tráfego para qualquer node.

6️⃣ Ativar sidecar injection
Namespace:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: apps
  labels:
    kuma.io/sidecar-injection: enabled
