Telecom operators (large ISPs and mobile carriers) running service meshes like Kuma generally don’t deploy zone-ingress on every node. That would create too many Envoy instances and too many BGP routes. Instead they use a collapsed ingress gateway layer with a small number of edge gateways per zone.

Below is the typical telecom-style Kuma architecture used when operating dozens to hundreds of clusters.

