3️⃣ Why Telecoms Avoid Per-Node Ingress

Running ingress on every node creates problems at scale.

Example cluster:

100 nodes
100 Envoy ingress
100 BGP routes

Routers dislike that.

Telecom pattern:

100 nodes
2 ingress gateways
1 Anycast VIP
2 BGP announcements

Much simpler routing table.

4️⃣ BGP Anycast Pattern

Routers advertise one VIP per zone.

Example:

VIP: 10.200.10.10

Announced by:

ingress-gw-a
ingress-gw-b

Routers choose closest gateway.

Traffic flow:

client
 → router
 → VIP
 → nearest gateway
 → mesh service

If one gateway dies:

BGP withdraw
traffic shifts automatically

No DNS change needed.

